In the retail sector, IBM recently introduced the “Smarter Commerce” platform to help traders lead the entire commercial cycle.
IBM also has a strong history in the Czech Republic.
In 1932, IBM established a branch in Czechoslovakia, the first country in Central and Eastern Europe.
Today, IBM <0xC4><0x8C>R also operates a strategic outsourcing center in Brno.
The Centre for Central and Eastern Europe is located in Prague and here there is also a top research team of world level, which deals with the technology of voice recognition.
