A slight exception was the period from 1962 to 1972, when it was also allowed to travel to Yugoslavia, then Yugoslavia took a pro-Western course and therefore the trips to Yugoslavia were severely restricted.
A great paradox of these socialist times was that it was not even allowed citizens of the Eastern Bloc (i.e. the Czechoslovaks) to travel freely within the framework of the socialist countries.
