This helped to complement the two different predecessor banks of UBS: a rich but sleepy bank with a focus on asset management in Zurich and a poorer but already more internationalised bank.
All of a sudden, the internationalized investment bankers came in cheaply with a lot of money, with which they could turn a huge wheel.
