"Wuffli, the highly intellectual, modest, who understands much of models and statistics, and Ospel, the abdominal man who has worked up from banking to the very top."
But Ospel finally relied on Wuffli.
And Wuffli probably made a crucial mistake in the end: "He thought his models were reality," Geiger says.
“This is a tragic case.”
Tragic, maybe.
It is clear that pride came before the case.
UBS employees recall clearly the executive meetings on which CEO Wuffli repeatedly issued the same slogan: Goldman Sachs is stepping down from the throne.
The American Bank was the most powerful investment bank in the world.
She led the "League Tables", the rankings that documented the success of the banks of that time.
The UBS wanted to go to the top.
