He had no beard, was dressed like a farmer in the area, wore no glasses and was much thinner.
Fingerprints do not lie.
Armed with a magnifying glass, ink, a planter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the body with those on the print sheet.
He had seen correctly: It was "Alfonso Cano".
